parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine wire harness insulation can cause electrical shorts, leading to engine stalling, fires, or other safety hazards, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Exposed electrical wires
crumbling or brittle wire insulation
electrical shorts
engine stalling
or fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage, loss of power, and potentially causing the engine to seize, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The temperature gauge is in the red zone
the coolant level is low
the coolant is leaking
the radiator fan is not working
the engine is overheating
the vehicle is losing power
the vehicle is producing a sweet or burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbo-charger failure can cause a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine is producing a loud whining or grinding noise
the engine is losing power
the vehicle is experiencing decreased fuel efficiency
the turbo-charger is leaking oil
the check engine light is illuminated
the vehicle is producing excessive smoke.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature wear of brake pads can lead to reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
excessive brake dust
brake pads wear down quickly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Vibration or pulsation when applying the brakes
squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
excessive brake dust
brake rotor surface is uneven or warped.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly surges or accelerates without pressing the gas pedal
often when braking or shifting gears
leading to unexpected and uncontrolled movement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents, loss of control, or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or stalls when shifting gears
the transmission slips or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission makes unusual noises
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission warning light illuminates on the dashboard.
